# Smart CRM Environment Variables
#
# IMPORTANT: This file is a template. Copy this to `.env` for local development.
# DO NOT commit `.env` file with real values to version control.

# =============================================================================
# FRONTEND (PUBLIC) VARIABLES - Safe to expose to client
# =============================================================================
# All variables that start with VITE_ are bundled into the frontend code
# and are accessible in the browser. NEVER put secrets here!

# Supabase Configuration (Public Keys Only)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# =============================================================================
# BACKEND (SERVER) VARIABLES - For Netlify Functions / Edge Functions Only
# =============================================================================
# These variables are ONLY available server-side in:
# - Netlify Functions (Functions tab in Netlify dashboard)
# - Supabase Edge Functions (automatically provided by Supabase)
#
# DO NOT prefix these with VITE_ as that would expose them to the frontend!

# ⚠️ CRITICAL: The following variables should ONLY be set in:
# 1. Netlify Dashboard: Site Settings > Environment Variables
# 2. Supabase automatically provides these to Edge Functions

# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here  # NEVER in .env!
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co         # Auto-provided by Supabase
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here                   # Auto-provided by Supabase

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file to `.env`:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Fill in the VITE_ variables with your Supabase project details:
#    - Get these from: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
#    - URL: Project Settings > API > Project URL
#    - Anon Key: Project Settings > API > anon/public key
#
# 3. NEVER add service_role keys to `.env`!

# NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT:
# 1. Go to: Site Settings > Environment Variables
# 2. Add the following variables:
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_URL (same as local)
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (same as local)
#
# 3. For Netlify Functions (if needed):
#    - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (from Supabase dashboard)
#    Note: Supabase Edge Functions automatically have access to these vars

# SUPABASE EDGE FUNCTIONS:
# Edge functions automatically have access to:
# - SUPABASE_URL
# - SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
# You don't need to configure these manually in Supabase.

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY CHECKLIST
# =============================================================================
# ✅ Only VITE_* variables in frontend code
# ✅ .env file is in .gitignore
# ✅ No service_role keys in frontend
# ✅ All required VITE_ vars defined in Netlify
# ✅ Netlify Functions have service_role key (if needed)
# ✅ Run `npm run validate` before committing

# =============================================================================
# VARIABLE NAMING CONVENTIONS
# =============================================================================
# VITE_*           - Public, bundled into frontend (safe to expose)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_*    - Not used (we use Vite, not Next.js)
# REACT_APP_*      - Not used (we use Vite, not Create React App)
# (no prefix)      - Server-only (Netlify Functions, Edge Functions)

# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================================================
# Error: "VITE_SUPABASE_URL is not defined"
#   → Check that .env file exists and contains VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#   → Restart dev server after editing .env
#
# Error: "VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY has role 'service_role'"
#   → You're using the service_role key instead of anon key
#   → Get the anon/public key from Supabase dashboard
#
# Error: "Supabase client not working in production"
#   → Check Netlify environment variables are set
#   → Ensure variable names match exactly (case-sensitive)
